This scripts runs basic sanity test for the LSI-3008 adapter.

Values to be passed in YMAL file:

Controller ID of the adapter, for which these tests will be executed.

Disks bay ID. i.e., both enclosure ID and slot ID, as shown below.
en:sn, where en --> enclosure ID, sn --> slot ID

Size: Size of the raid array, which you want to create

Spare: Slot of the disk, which should be hotspare

Please make sure that you place the Avago tool(SAS3IRCU) in the same location,
from where you are planning to run this script.
